<br>
If one of the major arguments / discussions we're having on this thread is taxes and how the Republicans versus the Democrats spend our tax money, maybe we're not even asking the right question.<br>
<br>
Maybe the question shouldn't be - how are tax dollars are spent by the Federal branch of the government, but WHY the Federal branch has become this huge self-serving, multiplying organism that seems to exist for no other reason than to devour your money and self-perpetuate.<br>
<br>
Hey, I'm no Nihilist, Anarchist, nor am I a member of the Libertarian party, but there needs to be a bigger distinction between the parties than how they feed at the tax trough.<br>
<br>
Insofar as Bush being a 'retard,' well no. Obviously not. He does have a degree from Yale and an MBA (I think Harvard but could be wrong). <br>
<br>
But for anybody who thinks: Alec Baldwin, Susan Sarandon, Michael Moore are somehow &quot;more intelligent&quot; you might want to do some research on the academic qualifications of those three.  Make sure you also do a Google on foreign posts they have held, leadership positions, and who briefs them daily. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shadowleaf>Shadowleaf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#330000>(7/6/03 2:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=824.topic&index=44>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just to add....</span><hr size=1> Dvaran. Your point makes no sense whatsoever. Clinton had no combat service, but then he didn't get up in front of the nation and yell 'Bring 'em on!'<br>
