<br>
I am British.  I lived in the USA for a few years and thoroughly enjoyed it.  Yes, it is a great country.  But here's some news for you: there are others!  Any of those countries Tibult listed also have their claims to being &quot;great&quot;.  I loved many things about America - the friendliness of most people, the personal freedoms, the largely laissez-faire economic policies and the general will of large segments of society to do the best they can for THEMSELVES.  I hated some things too.  The level of violence in particular.  The still too prevalent undertones of racism.  The amazingly low level of intelligent news reporting and commentary.  The lack of any real demarcation between the political parties.  And more than anything else the general ignorance of the world outside your borders.<br>
<br>
Maybe if more Americans applied for a passport and got abroad more than the occasional trip to Canada or Mexico they'd have a more balanced view of the world.  Throwing around bullshit comments along the lines of &quot;if you don't like it, get the fuck out&quot; is a great way to immediately remove any shred of credibility from what you are saying.  You can love your country without having to love everything about it - nowhere in the world is perfect, and all convincing yourself otherwise achieves is to make it far less likely that the problems you DO have will be solved. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aiaka>Aiaka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://209.108.162.247/dancer.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 836<br> <font color=#330000>(7/7/03 8:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=824.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just to add....</span><hr size=1> I have been a few places, Mexico, Bahamas, France, Italy, and soon England I hope.  I can tell you for one I kiss the ground when I get home.  It is great to visit other places and I love the culture and new things but I love being back home in the USA.  Do I agree with everything the government does?  Nope, never have and most likely never will.<br>
However when someone says they want out, what is keeping them here?  Save up some money and take a trip to see where you want to go, find a job there and move.  I think they are pretty much blowing off steam and just saying it for a reaction.  Just like people who say you don't like it get the hell out are saying it to get a reaction out of the person who hates the country so much.  I have said it before and my reason is, you are free to leave anytime you want, so what is stopping you or are you just tossing out BS to bluff, well sparky I am calling your bluff, leave!<br>
Its not that they are mindless government drones they are sick of hearing everyone bitch and moan about a country that most of us still love.  Freedom isn't free it comes with a very high price, a price of the lives of men and women most of the time who have sworn to defend this freedom so many take for granted.  People don't like war, I don't know of anyone who loves war, my grandfather close to the end of his life had many nightmares about when he served in the army in WW2.  The things he would tell me from his dreams kept me up at night almost in tears that the most wonderful person I have ever known had to live through that hell and the fact he felt guilty he couldn't save his younger brother from being killed.  That was something he had to carry his entire life, but he did and when asked if he regretted it he said not at all because I got to watch my children and my grandchildren grow up in a better world because of it and I know my brother would have loved to be here watching you all grow up but he died doing what he loved, defending a country he loved.<br>
You may not like war, you may not like many things, but sometimes just sometimes it is needed.  And please remember that our government leaders have more information on what is really going on in Iraq than any of us will ever know, have a little faith, and weather you like it or not please, please support the troops who have been through the hell of war and seen things we could not imagine in a million years. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
